Outcome of Endoscopic Endonasal Surgery in Pediatric Craniopharyngiomas.

Mazzatenta D(1), Zoli M(2), Guaraldi F(1), Ambrosi F(3), Faustini Fustini M(4), 
Pasquini E(5), Asioli S(3), Zucchelli M(6).

Author information:
(1)Center for Diagnosis and Treatment of Pituitary and Skull Base Tumors 
(Pituitary Unit), IRCCS Istituto delle Scienze Neurologiche di Bologna, Bologna, 
Italy; Department of Biomedical and Neuromotor Sciences, University of Bologna, 
Bologna, Italy.
(2)Center for Diagnosis and Treatment of Pituitary and Skull Base Tumors 
(Pituitary Unit), IRCCS Istituto delle Scienze Neurologiche di Bologna, Bologna, 
Italy; Department of Biomedical and Neuromotor Sciences, University of Bologna, 
Bologna, Italy. Electronic address: matteo.zoli4@unibo.it.
(3)Department of Biomedical and Neuromuscular Sciences, Section of Anatomic 
Pathology "M. Malpighi" at Bellaria Hospital, University of Bologna, Bologna, 
Italy.
(4)Center for Diagnosis and Treatment of Pituitary and Skull Base Tumors 
(Pituitary Unit), IRCCS Istituto delle Scienze Neurologiche di Bologna, Bologna, 
